Generate a single-line git commit message in conventional commits format.
Output ONLY the commit message — no explanation, no quotes, no code fences.

A "Branch:" line may appear at the top of the diff. If it contains a Jira
ticket key (e.g. ABC-123), prepend it to the description separated by a space.

Format (with ticket):    type(scope): TICKET-KEY description
Format (without ticket): type(scope): description

Rules:
- Under 72 characters total
- Use the correct type and scope from the diff
- Scope is REQUIRED: choose the primary component or subsystem
- Valid types: feat, fix, refactor, chore, ci, build, test, docs, style, perf
- A Jira ticket key matches: one or more uppercase letters, a hyphen, then digits (e.g. ABC-1, PROJ-42)
- The description must be factually accurate and professional
- Imperative mood

Examples (do NOT copy literally — generate from the actual diff):
  feat(auth): ABC-123 add JWT refresh token support
  fix(api): PROJ-42 correct null pointer in user lookup
  chore(deps): update dependencies per security advisory
  refactor(config): MY-99 extract profile loading into helper
